        <p>WhisperKOOL 8000 ducted split on a 2,800-bottle ocean-view cellar. Compressor short-cycling on low-pressure switch — classic low refrigerant symptom. Electronic leak detection found a slow leak at the evaporator distributor tube, likely from vibration over 8 years of service. Refrigerant charge (R-404A) was 18% below spec.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Recovered remaining R-404A per EPA, replaced the distributor assembly, pulled 500-micron vacuum, weighed in fresh charge to factory spec. Leak-checked condenser at 150 PSI nitrogen — clean. Pulled down from 68°F to 56°F over 6 hours, stable thereafter. Brought a portable spot cooler for the customer's most valuable case while we waited for the vacuum. Total downtime for the collection: about 7 hours above 60°F.</div>
