        <h3>"Cellar is at 70°F, humidity at 30% — has been drifting for a week"</h3>
        <p>2,000-bottle cellar with a 14-year-old Wine Guardian condensing unit. Ambient garage 78°F, cellar 70°F and climbing, RH at 30% (humidifier had also failed). Condensing unit compressor had failed — stuck on thermal and not restarting. Given age and the state of the evaporator fan motor and control contactor, the math was a replacement, not a repair.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Installed Wine Guardian D088 replacement matched to the existing line set and evaporator. Pressure-tested line set at 300 PSI nitrogen, pulled vacuum to 400 microns, weighed in R-134a to spec. Humidifier reservoir cleaned and restarted. Cellar recovered to 55°F and 62% RH within 14 hours. Customer had moved 40 most-valuable bottles to a guest-house fridge during the drift; the rest of the 2,000 stayed put and were within acceptable temperature range the entire time.</div>
